text: RT @nixxin: Facebook might not know of all the users whose data has been breached here but some users have checked their data via some of t‚Ä¶
retweet_text:
Facebook might not know of all the users whose data has been breached here but some users have checked their data via some of these sites, like the one by @troyhunt. Why can't facebook inform at least those people that these sites know about? Best efforts basis?
4/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
RT @nixxin: Out whether our data has been leaked (mine hasn't). Millions of people do not. They deserve to know.

It is Facebook's responsi‚Ä¶
retweet_text:
Out whether our data has been leaked (mine hasn't). Millions of people do not. They deserve to know.

It is Facebook's responsibility to inform users. Even if passwords haven't been scraped. This data can be used with other data. Users need to be warned of risks 
3/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: RT @nixxin: Frankly it's ridiculous that Facebook can even choose not to notify users that their data can be breached. Should be illegal. I‚Ä¶
retweet_text:
Frankly it's ridiculous that Facebook can even choose not to notify users that their data can be breached. Should be illegal. It shouldn't be their choice. It's not their data.

You & I might read the news & know abt the breach. We might know how to find sites that help us
2/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: RT @nixxin: It's an absolute shame that Facebook is not notifying users that their data has been breached. This impacts 500 million users w‚Ä¶
retweet_text:
It's an absolute shame that Facebook is not notifying users that their data has been breached. This impacts 500 million users worldwide, and from what I've read and an estimated 6.1 million in India. 

1/n

text: might be because of the performance throttling as there are no fans on the MBA along with the 7 core CPU. Though you cannot expect much of a difference in terms of the user experience, but if you are into video editing, then I would suggest the Mac Mini over the MBA for sure 5/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
GPU on the MacBook Air offered as the base configuration. For us, these machines took 3-4 weeks to get delivered, unlike the custom ones that were quoted 3 months wait period where I just wanted RAM upgrade, though skipped now.

In terms of the performance, the big difference 4/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: The same video exported in Full HD 60 FPS under ProRes quality took 9 minutes, 27 seconds on the Macbook Air M1, while the same took just 3 minutes & 22 seconds on the Mac Mini. The only difference between both is the GPU which is 8 core on the Mac Mini, unlike the 7 core  3/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
First off we ran the @geekbench benchmarks that showed both of the machines had scored very close but the real difference was experienced only when we started rendering videos.

We used the Final Cut Pro app & exported the same videos simultaneously & were very surprised 2/n https://t.co/VD10NUDvTI

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
Whatsapp Crashing on iOS14?
Here's the solution I found.

Solution - Remove permission to Photos from Settings > WhatsApp > Photos > Allow Photos Access > None

If device is connected to your PC through WhatsApp web, you can still access the chat, but the above solution works.

Go to Settings > Accessibility > Touch > Back Tap

Select any option from the list. 
I have selected Home & Notifications Center because that saves time & efforts. 

Now just Double or Triple Tap on the back of the phone to enable.

Steps in Earlier Tweet. https://t.co/JDs0MBBvzT

text:
Wanted to thank the Society Management taking care of all these things during these stressful times & we all volunteers who are making sure everyone gets groceries on time.

Special thanks to the @telanganaCMO Govt who sent their medical reps to each flat to check our health. üôè

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
This second case makes the logistics even more tougher. This is the reason It is important to self declare the travel schedules but many folks not coming forward. 

Wishes to the whole family for speedy recovery. 

Will keep you all posted on this specific case.

name: Amit Bhawani
text: Since one of them is an elderly kid they are managing themselves with the support our society has given them since morning. Taken the same route as they have gone out. Fumigation and sanitization happened today evening so no need for one more round of sanitization.

name: Amit Bhawani
text: Doctors refused to get the kids admitted because there are no symptoms. They have taken the B1 & walked all the way to the gate. They have taken the stairs & used the gloves. They took utmost care not to touch anything. Kids came back today early morning & locked themselves up.

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
Ma‚Äôam (his Wife) (P40) didn‚Äôt show any symptoms initially but felt uneasy y‚Äôday. So she called Continental and got the ambulance and shifted to Continental y‚Äôday midnight.

She went to the hospital along with the kids.They along with the kids have used the ambulance.

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
They didn‚Äôt perform any testing on him so he came back He went to hospital on Monday, the 23rd and got admitted. All the time, he went thru the stairs to B1 and used his car. He used the gloves and took utmost care not to touch anything.

His family was at home, but ...

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
He came home & locked himself along with his family from the 17th night. All the elevators were sanitized from 18th Morning. No maid, no cook was allowed inside the house. No one went in and no one came out of the house.

He was advised to go to Gachibowli on Saturday by police.

name: Amit Bhawani
text: The society is in complete lock down with all 1100 flats. The Gentleman was away in London for a week and returned to his home on 17th Night 8PM. He didn‚Äôt show any symptoms at the time of landing so officials asked him to go home and do self quarantine.

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
A Week of Society Lock down after two Positive #CoronaVirus cases. Here's our story

I live in a society in Kokapet, Hyderabad where last week we got a confirmation that one person (P34) has been testing positive for #corona from & situation have turned completely from that day. https://t.co/9mN0RlDQm3

text:
while the entrepreneur's good luck on the business they are into & the reality friends a prosperous year because Hyderabad is booming & I feel we should we see great results on the investments by the next decade.

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
I have ventured into Real Estate, Trading, Blogging, Vlogging & eCommerce Store all of which probably need full attention & my focus for the year is to give proper time to each of these. 

I also wish all the creators an amazing year for the content they create ... 3/4

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
When I look back at 2019, it was one of the good years in terms of business, life, health but I would like to welcome the new decade with open hands for all the challenges ahead. 

There's a saying, "never put all the eggs in one basket", which I have been following and .. 2/4

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
Wishing you all a #HappyNewYear from our family to yours.

Instead of the yearly ritual of making resolutions that we tend to forget in a week let's make little goals and note them on a piece of paper & try to complete them one by one. 

#Welcome2020 #2020NewYear #Happy2020 1/4 https://t.co/LXg2z46toV

text:
This is the same experience when it comes to Laptops, Smartphones where many brands make their loyal customers run around for service because once a product is sold, it's not their problem. 

Wondering will this change?

name: Amit Bhawani
text: The problem is that the Dealer just does not care about service once sold while brands could take care of at least pick up and drop from the customer & probably post checking the unit, send a brand new unit because the drives clearly would show the usage hours & here's its DOA.

text:

Ordered 2 Brand New 8TB HDD for my NAS & one of them was "Dead on Arrival". The dealer asked us to contact @westerndigital who then want us to courier to Bangalore & expect re-certified drive & not new one. üòê

name: Amit Bhawani
text: @lazykid2004 Exactly my point. The problem is that with that phrase they are getting a lot of positive attention that there are no ads but people are not understanding the difference.

name: Amit Bhawani
text: @LegendGPV @s_anuj The devices which we have are sent to us by the @XiaomiIndia Team & we never covered the Chinese variants.

name: Amit Bhawani
text: As I have myself said in the video, the pricing is little higher but the specs aren't bad and #RedmiK20 is a good product but the Ads in the device is something not acceptable when they compare their products to Apple, Samsung & OnePlus who don't spam their users.

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
There are different types of ads that run on their smartphones & they had mentioned about "Display ads" which is just one type of ad, but media starting calling out that there are no ads.

There is a difference & that difference will kill the experience of the buyers.

name: Amit Bhawani
text: @SatheeshGalla Partially you are right but then when the brand themselves promise there would be no ads, how is this acceptable?

name: Amit Bhawani
text: @yogesh_m_ Flashing is not something everyone can do and when the brand says there are no Ads, this is not acceptable.

name: Amit Bhawani

name: Amit Bhawani
text: At the current price point, the #OnePlus7 is a good package for anyone who is looking for a good flagship device but the #OnePlus7Pro's pricing brings in the sentiment that they have increased the prices. Users still get the 33K option which is aggressively priced 5/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: We have been hearing that they might launch the #OnePlusTV & based on the current portfolio we can presume that they would come with a proper TV that supports all the services & this is what happens when a brand brings consistency towards the portfolio. 4/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: The accessories they launch are very good in terms of quality, minimal branding that makes even the competition to use them (Based on what I have seen) & the availability of the important accessories on the official website gives their customers easy access 3/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: Anyone who owns the earlier models like the #OnePlus3 are also getting the latest software updates and are still satisfied. This hints at the long life of the phones same as the iPhone's where users are not needed to upgrade almost every year. 2/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
Thanks for the feedback everyone.

In my opinion, #OnePlus has definitely made sure they satisfy the needs of their customers though yes they have been increasing the prices of their phones while the Oxygen OS & Branding are two reasons why they sell & are recommended 1/n

name: Amit Bhawani

name: Amit Bhawani
text: I have personally never liked MIUI but then there are more than a 100 Million users who love it, so its a personal opinion but MIUI is filled with many little utility features that are useful & this makes people not switch to other smartphones 6/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: In terms of the service support, I have read many bad experiences in the past but now things are improving and people have been sharing lesser complains that hints are better products or better support. This is a good thing for everyone. 5/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: With the current portfolio if I had to recommend someone a budget smartphone, might recommend a @RedmiIndia but when it goes over 30K can't recommend & this is where the brand should focus on brand positioning. 4/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: Regarding the Ads, the brand has clearly informed that they are part of their business & we won't see them removing the same anytime soon. Here's a video on the same https://t.co/sSOx6iWc95 3/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text: the consumers happy with products that are valued for their money & that are not overpriced. That said, I feel that they should bring more of their IOT products in India that are sold in China though there might not be a big market for the same at the moment. 2/n

name: Amit Bhawani
text:
Thanks for the feedback, do tag your friends who own Xiaomi products for their opinions.

In my opinion, I would say that if @XiaomiIndia is maintaining #1 position, it is because of @manukumarjain & their team who have been launching products in every price point making 1/n

text:

text:

With the number of Smartphones launching in recent weeks I feel the buyers are now, not only getting confused but also bored with the available options. 

There are a few brands like OnePlus, Asus who don't flood the market but others need a break.
